479
00:25:34,909 --> 00:25:37,035
Can we magnify times five?

480
00:25:40,247 --> 00:25:42,123
That's not a gallstone.

481
00:25:43,167 --> 00:25:46,002
His liver's completely
filled with worms.

482
00:25:49,048 --> 00:25:51,799
You have strongyloides,
also known as threadworms.

483
00:25:51,884 --> 00:25:54,636
They disseminated all over your
body, causing all your symptoms.

484
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:55,887
How'd I get a parasite?

485
00:25:55,971 --> 00:25:59,807
Most likely through sexual
activity, but we can't be sure.

486
00:26:00,768 --> 00:26:02,560
And what's the treatment?

487
00:26:02,645 --> 00:26:04,062
Two mebendazole pills.

488
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:07,357
That's it?

489
00:26:07,441 --> 00:26:10,985
You'll be fine. Your liver, too.
Go back to your lives.

490
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:20,078
You know this is
the doctors' lounge.

491
00:26:20,162 --> 00:26:21,287
I know.

492
00:26:21,747 --> 00:26:24,999
It seemed like the place
to read doctors' notes.

493
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:27,502
You are good at it, by the way.

494
00:26:28,837 --> 00:26:31,130
Why are you reading my charts?

495
00:26:31,423 --> 00:26:34,133
Because I'm worried
about my girlfriend.

496
00:26:34,843 --> 00:26:37,887
Your girlfriend is
a male porn star?

497
00:26:37,972 --> 00:26:39,472
No, I'm dating Lisa Cuddy.

498
00:26:39,974 --> 00:26:41,766
Seriously? Cool, huh?

499
00:26:41,850 --> 00:26:44,290
And if House doesn't have his
team, that'll make her miserable,

500
00:26:44,311 --> 00:26:45,895
which will make me miserable.

501
00:26:45,980 --> 00:26:50,400
Which brings us to the fact that you
have elevated noting to an art form.

502
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:51,734
I see the connection.

503
00:26:51,819 --> 00:26:53,111
Most doctors write "9:00 a.m."

504
00:26:53,195 --> 00:26:54,779
if they scrub in at 9:00
or anything near it.

505
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:59,450
You write "9:03" and you make little
notations when procedures are delayed.

506
00:26:59,660 --> 00:27:01,369
You're easily impressed.

507
00:27:01,453 --> 00:27:04,080
Well, yeah. I was.

508
00:27:04,164 --> 00:27:08,126
Until I saw that you had virtually stopped
writing them about four weeks ago.

509
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:09,627
Been busy. Got a backlog.

510
00:27:09,712 --> 00:27:15,300
Yeah, people with your level of precision
don't really just get backlogs.

511
00:27:17,344 --> 00:27:20,305
No one knows why
you're leaving PPTH.

512
00:27:20,389 --> 00:27:21,681
Because it's personal.

513
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:23,474
If something happened...

514
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:26,894
I mean, if you're leaving to get away
from something that you did, or she did,

515
00:27:26,979 --> 00:27:28,646
or both of you did...

516
00:27:28,731 --> 00:27:31,899
I mean, emotionally, maybe you want
to run away, but in my experience,

517
00:27:31,984 --> 00:27:35,987
if you're staring at a pit
bull in some guy's back yard,

518
00:27:36,739 --> 00:27:39,157
you're better off staying
right where you are.

519
00:27:39,241 --> 00:27:42,493
Face the problem, that way it
can't bite you in the ass.

520
00:27:47,041 --> 00:27:49,334
Thanks for the folksy wisdom.

521
00:27:50,753 --> 00:27:53,755
Hey, you got any dirt
on any of the other three?

522
00:27:54,131 --> 00:27:56,090
It'd really help me out.

523
00:28:01,764 --> 00:28:03,514
I thought you said those two
pills was all he needed.

524
00:28:03,599 --> 00:28:04,599
Lungs are filling with fluid.

525
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:06,934
Suction him and
get him on oxygen.

526
00:28:12,107 --> 00:28:15,693
Patient's lungs are severely
compromised, liver's still failing.

527
00:28:15,778 --> 00:28:17,820
Worms could easily
have been a coincidence.

528
00:28:17,905 --> 00:28:19,625
Almost be surprising
if he didn't have them.

529
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:23,368
Which means it could be a
hematological problem plus cardiomyopathy.

530
00:28:23,452 --> 00:28:26,871
No. Neck veins are flat,
precordial exam was normal.

531
00:28:26,955 --> 00:28:28,664
What if it's lymphoma?

532
00:28:28,749 --> 00:28:31,542
Peritoneal carcinomatosis
explains the liver failure,

533
00:28:31,627 --> 00:28:34,962
paraneoplastic syndrome
explains everything else.

534
00:28:36,465 --> 00:28:39,884
Lymphoma it is.
Prep him for chemo.

535
00:28:40,803 --> 00:28:44,097
Fax Taub and Thirteen the
latest update on the case.

536
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:48,643
Seriously?

537
00:28:49,645 --> 00:28:51,229
They have as much right to
know as anyone on the team.

538
00:28:51,313 --> 00:28:53,648
You either like the
diagnosis or you don't.

539
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:57,527
If you don't, we need to keep talking.
If you do, you need to shut up.

540
00:28:57,611 --> 00:29:00,321
What we don't need
is this stupid game.

541
00:29:08,205 --> 00:29:10,206
You're mad at House,
but you're not mad at me.

542
00:29:10,290 --> 00:29:12,667
Do you want me
to be mad at you?

543
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:14,669
You blame House, not me.

544
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:16,796
I'm mad at House
because he's an ass.

545
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:19,924
And I am mad at you, but I
don't want to leave you.

546
00:29:20,008 --> 00:29:23,761
What I did may be the worst thing
I ever did, it may be the best.

547
00:29:23,846 --> 00:29:26,848
I'm either a murderer or a guy
who stopped a mass murderer.

548
00:29:26,932 --> 00:29:28,975
But I did it. Me.

549
00:29:29,768 --> 00:29:32,937
And even if it destroys me,
I'd do it again today.

550
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:34,355
You don't mean that.
This isn't you...

551
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:36,847
I'm not running away
from what I did because

552
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:39,277
you want to pretend
I never did it.

553
00:29:41,655 --> 00:29:43,698
If that's how you feel,

554
00:29:46,326 --> 00:29:47,535
okay.

555
00:29:52,499 --> 00:29:55,126
My strategy is not
completely working.

556
00:29:56,628 --> 00:29:59,547
All four of them
want to work for me,

557
00:29:59,631 --> 00:30:02,800
but all four of them have reasons
why they don't want to work for me.

558
00:30:02,885 --> 00:30:07,221
How do I get them to take one from
column A and none from column B?

559
00:30:12,186 --> 00:30:13,436
Right.

560
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:16,772
Right, by not saying anything, you're
saying that the answer's inside me?

561
00:30:16,857 --> 00:30:18,983
The answer has nothing
to do with the question.

562
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:20,860
Then it's not
technically the answer.

563
00:30:20,944 --> 00:30:22,820
Why do you need
three of these doctors?

564
00:30:22,905 --> 00:30:28,284
Because I know they're good. Other doctors
fall into the might-be-good category.

565
00:30:28,368 --> 00:30:30,008
It has nothing to do
with them being good,

566
00:30:30,078 --> 00:30:31,787
you think they're
idiots half the time.

567
00:30:31,872 --> 00:30:33,831
But they're comfortable.
You feel abandoned by Cuddy,

568
00:30:33,916 --> 00:30:37,335
so you're reaching out to
people you know for comfort.

569
00:30:37,419 --> 00:30:41,047
Oh, my God, you're right.
I don't need doctors at all.

570
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:43,841
I just need a good friend.

571
00:30:45,260 --> 00:30:46,260
Cuddy's right.

572
00:30:46,345 --> 00:30:49,263
Maybe, just maybe, if I don't
play along, you'll realize

573
00:30:49,348 --> 00:30:52,892
you can't solve a deeper problem
with a surface solution.

574
00:30:53,602 --> 00:30:57,188
Would've been more profound
if you hadn't said anything.

575
00:30:59,441 --> 00:31:00,858
You okay?

576
00:31:00,943 --> 00:31:02,318
Getting through it.

577
00:31:02,402 --> 00:31:04,862
Be a lot easier once you
two are away from here.

578
00:31:04,947 --> 00:31:06,113
Yeah.

579
00:31:09,785 --> 00:31:11,494
He's peeing blood.

580
00:31:11,787 --> 00:31:12,828
BP's rising.

581
00:31:12,913 --> 00:31:13,996
Heart rate is up to 250.

582
00:31:14,081 --> 00:31:16,165
He's going into cardiac arrest.

583
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:20,253
Charging. Clear.

584
00:31:20,712 --> 00:31:21,712
He's bleeding out.

585
00:31:21,797 --> 00:31:23,339
His body's
completely giving out.

586
00:31:23,423 --> 00:31:25,049
Charging. Clear.

587
00:31:27,135 --> 00:31:28,219
We've got him stabilized,

588
00:31:28,303 --> 00:31:30,221
but no red cells,
no white cells,

589
00:31:30,305 --> 00:31:31,806
practically no
platelets either.

590
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:34,684
Mebendazole can cause adverse
effects, but nothing like this.

591
00:31:34,768 --> 00:31:37,353
He's been off it
since yesterday anyway.

592
00:31:38,981 --> 00:31:42,733
Long passes, wild
guesses, anything.

593
00:31:42,818 --> 00:31:45,861
Hypopituitarism? Could cause
multi-organ failure if...

594
00:31:45,946 --> 00:31:48,406
If his thyroid hormone
wasn't completely normal.

595
00:31:48,490 --> 00:31:49,907
Renal cell carcinoma.

596
00:31:49,992 --> 00:31:51,409
Renal ultrasound was clean.

597
00:31:51,493 --> 00:31:53,828
I'd say aleukemic leukemia,

598
00:31:53,912 --> 00:31:55,538
marrow's not making
enough normal cells, but...

599
00:31:55,622 --> 00:31:59,333
Ablate the patient's bone
marrow, find him a donor match.

600
00:32:00,168 --> 00:32:02,378
You want to nuke
the patient's marrow?

601
00:32:02,462 --> 00:32:04,714
He had no evidence of being
anemic or immune-compromised

602
00:32:04,798 --> 00:32:06,716
when he was admitted...
Perfect white count as well.

603
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:08,092
Ablation
could kill him,

604
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:11,178
or leave him defenseless against
an infection that could.

605
00:32:11,263 --> 00:32:13,764
Then come up with
something better.

606
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:21,188
He may as well die
while we're treating him.

607
00:32:22,524 --> 00:32:26,569
Okay with you if I bring the other
candidates into the loop now?

608
00:32:30,282 --> 00:32:32,575
The risks,
they're really minimal.

609
00:32:32,659 --> 00:32:35,703
We'll do a series
of painless injections...

610
00:32:37,039 --> 00:32:38,372
Excuse me.

611
00:32:41,627 --> 00:32:43,387
The whole thing can be
done as an outpatient.

612
00:32:59,645 --> 00:33:01,896
You're leaving at 11:00 a.m.?

613
00:33:02,689 --> 00:33:05,107
Trust me, the case
is almost over.

614
00:33:06,026 --> 00:33:08,653
Foreman told me you're
ablating the patient's marrow

615
00:33:08,737 --> 00:33:11,739
on a non-theory that
Foreman himself withdrew.

616
00:33:11,865 --> 00:33:14,200
You're gonna kill the patient.

617
00:33:15,702 --> 00:33:17,912
Is this about me and Lucas?

618
00:33:21,083 --> 00:33:22,958
I want alternatives
for the patient.

619
00:33:23,043 --> 00:33:24,251
So do I.

620
00:33:33,929 --> 00:33:36,097
I want to be on the team.

621
00:33:42,562 --> 00:33:45,439
You think that's gonna
save your marriage?

622
00:33:48,944 --> 00:33:50,444
I don't know.

623
00:33:53,782 --> 00:33:56,117
Four candidates, three spots.

624
00:33:58,036 --> 00:34:00,413
I got a tough decision
ahead of me.

625
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:29,316
Hi. Remy, this is Dr. Turner
from the Pennsauken Free Clinic.

626
00:34:29,401 --> 00:34:32,987
We all loved meeting you,
and the job's yours.

627
00:34:33,071 --> 00:34:35,823
Call me back,
let's pick a start date.

628
00:34:51,173 --> 00:34:55,426
I want it to look natural. I
mean, much younger, but natural.

629
00:34:55,510 --> 00:34:57,553
Can you get rid of the
crow's feet altogether?

630
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:59,722
Or is it better to
leave a trace of them?

631
00:34:59,806 --> 00:35:02,433
I don't look old enough
to have them anyway, do I?

632
00:35:02,517 --> 00:35:03,601
Absolutely.

633
00:35:03,685 --> 00:35:05,060
I do look old enough?

634
00:35:05,145 --> 00:35:06,145
No.

635
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:10,357
I'm sorry. Hang on a second.

636
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:20,242
Why are you here?

637
00:35:20,327 --> 00:35:24,497
Because I think we're wrong, which
means something's gonna go wrong.

638
00:35:26,792 --> 00:35:28,125
Or right.

639
00:35:28,210 --> 00:35:29,293
Takayama here.

640
00:35:29,377 --> 00:35:31,545
It's me and Thirteen,
stop the ablation.

641
00:35:34,674 --> 00:35:35,758
Because...

642
00:35:35,842 --> 00:35:36,963
Those threadworms.

643
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:39,845
Why would his body have gone to hell
just hours after they were gone?

644
00:35:39,930 --> 00:35:42,010
The worms weren't hurting him,
they were helping him.

645
00:35:42,057 --> 00:35:44,308
He has extra-intestinal Crohn's.

646
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:46,644
He got it from being
raised in too clean,

647
00:35:46,728 --> 00:35:48,479
too overprotective
of an environment.

648
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:49,814
It's the hygiene hypothesis,

649
00:35:49,898 --> 00:35:52,338
why there's so much autoimmune
disease in the developed world,

650
00:35:52,359 --> 00:35:53,984
and almost none in
the developing world.

651
00:35:54,069 --> 00:35:56,153
The worms were keeping
the Crohn's in check,

652
00:35:56,238 --> 00:35:58,144
teaching his immune
system what it should've

653
00:35:58,157 --> 00:36:00,074
learned from eating
dirt growing up.

654
00:36:00,158 --> 00:36:02,409
Once you killed them,
it started killing him.

655
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:08,207
So his life of filth wasn't the
problem, the clean living was.

656
00:36:09,084 --> 00:36:10,835
We'll start him
on methylprednisolone.

657
00:36:10,919 --> 00:36:12,711
And some helminths.

658
00:36:14,714 --> 00:36:16,924
Worms. Cool, huh?

659
00:36:18,927 --> 00:36:20,719
Best out of three?

660
00:36:25,100 --> 00:36:27,226
Have
you been a bad boy?

661
00:36:31,815 --> 00:36:33,357
Yeah, that's...

662
00:36:38,780 --> 00:36:40,948
I want to be on the team.

663
00:36:41,032 --> 00:36:42,366
Good news for your wife.

664
00:36:43,201 --> 00:36:45,202
Thanks for the sarcasm.

665
00:36:45,287 --> 00:36:48,873
I reorganized my life
to spend more time with her,

666
00:36:48,957 --> 00:36:51,542
but apparently I don't love
her as much as I thought.

667
00:36:51,626 --> 00:36:53,544
Or you love her more.

668
00:36:54,129 --> 00:36:58,340
This job gives you the thrill you
used to find through philandering.

669
00:36:59,885 --> 00:37:01,886
Better to cheat with
a beaker and an MRI

670
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:05,639
than one of your platinum-blonde
plastic surgery patients.

671
00:37:07,809 --> 00:37:09,476
I'll let you know.

672
00:37:28,330 --> 00:37:31,165
I told House I want to
work for him again.

673
00:37:32,834 --> 00:37:34,501
Stay on the team.

674
00:37:35,503 --> 00:37:37,087
You were always
more into it than I was,

675
00:37:37,172 --> 00:37:39,882
more interested in diagnostics.

676
00:37:40,634 --> 00:37:43,636
Unless House was right
about why you want out.

677
00:37:53,980 --> 00:37:55,522
Four for four.

678
00:38:02,656 --> 00:38:04,531
I was in love with you.

679
00:38:05,784 --> 00:38:07,326
I was an idiot.

680
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:10,579
Tried to be like you,
tried to understand you,

681
00:38:10,664 --> 00:38:13,707
because I thought
I could heal you.

682
00:38:17,545 --> 00:38:19,213
You almost killed that patient.

683
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:21,256
If almost not saving
his life means...

684
00:38:21,341 --> 00:38:23,467
You knew the diagnosis
a long time ago.

685
00:38:23,551 --> 00:38:26,595
You risked another patient's
life to bait your old team.

686
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:28,138
Another one?

687
00:38:28,223 --> 00:38:29,598
You did kill Dibala.

688
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:33,477
By playing God and teaching
us to do the same.

689
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:35,145
I taught you to think
for yourselves.

690
00:38:35,230 --> 00:38:36,480
You don't even think
of them as people,

691
00:38:36,564 --> 00:38:39,066
they're just lab rats
for your little puzzles.

692
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:40,401
You celebrate their humanity,

693
00:38:40,485 --> 00:38:42,820
I'd rather solve those little
puzzles and save their lives.

694
00:38:42,904 --> 00:38:46,073
Motives do matter.
Lives can't come second.

695
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:48,826
The patient is alive.
That's what matters.

696
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:50,327
Not to you.

697
00:38:50,412 --> 00:38:54,164
All you care about is that Taub
and Thirteen fell for your game.

698
00:38:54,249 --> 00:38:57,376
You'll poison them
just like you poisoned Chase.

699
00:38:58,420 --> 00:39:02,256
Your husband killed a patient
and you're breaking up with me?

700
00:39:03,842 --> 00:39:05,384
You ruined him,

701
00:39:08,722 --> 00:39:11,432
so he can't even see
right from wrong,

702
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:16,061
can't even see the sanctity
of a human life any more.

703
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:24,445
I loved you, and I loved Chase.

704
00:39:26,781 --> 00:39:28,657
I'm sorry for you both,

705
00:39:30,035 --> 00:39:32,244
for who you've become because

706
00:39:34,622 --> 00:39:37,249
there's no way back
for either of you.

707
00:40:42,232 --> 00:40:46,568
Any idea where I can get a great
big "Mission Accomplished" banner?

708
00:40:48,863 --> 00:40:53,367
Got my sanity back, my
license back, and now...

709
00:40:55,036 --> 00:40:57,204
You're kidding. All of them?

710
00:40:57,288 --> 00:40:58,956
Three out of four,

711
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:01,625
which is almost as good
as four out of five.

712
00:41:01,709 --> 00:41:03,919
Who was the... Cameron.

713
00:41:04,003 --> 00:41:06,630
Wow. I can't believe it.

714
00:41:06,714 --> 00:41:11,552
I mean, really.
I can't believe it.

715
00:41:14,305 --> 00:41:16,890
You were right, House.
Good for you.

716
00:41:17,559 --> 00:41:19,059
Yeah. It is.

717
00:41:21,646 --> 00:41:25,983
She's broken up with Chase, and
she's leaving the hospital. Still,

718
00:41:26,609 --> 00:41:28,861
three out of four ain't bad.

